                  <list>
                    <item>
                      <p>Vellum, about 7 1/4 in. by 5, consisting of 31 leaves (Add. 17,168, foll.
                        154—184). The quires, three in number, are now signed with letters from $ܝܙ
                        to $ܝܛ. There are from 20 to 26 lines in each page. This manuscript is
                        written in a neat, regular hand of the ixth cent.</p>
                    </item>
